## Description

This pull request addresses the issue where unhandled errors in middleware could cause the server to crash. The current behavior terminates the server without handling the error, leading to an incomplete response to the client.

## Proposed Solution

To handle unhandled errors in middleware, I have made changes to the `lib/router/layer.js` file. Specifically, I modified lines 95-101 to include an error handling block. This ensures that errors occurring within middleware are caught and can be handled appropriately.

## Code Changes

Here is an example of the modified code:

```javascript
app.use((error, req, res, next) => {
  // Handle the error appropriately, e.g., log the error, send an error response, etc.
  // ...
})

import { PrismaHelper } from "../infra/db/prisma/prisma";
import app from './config/app'
import { exec } from 'node:child_process'

const main = async () => {
